Instructions to install the CLI in windows:
    *. Make sure codetuner-1.0-SNAPSHOT-all.jar is present in the directory. If not, run gradlew shadowJar in the main project directory.
    *. Add this directory to the windows path.
    *. Open command prompt and type codetuner --help to see the list of commands.
    *. To run the CLI, type codetuner <command> <options> as shown in the help menu.

Make sure java is installed in your system and JAVA_HOME is set to the java installation directory. This works best with java 18. Might work with other versions too.